context: The southern side of Miami includes Coral Way, <a0_0><b5_0>The Roads<b5_0/><a0_0/> and Coconut Grove. Coral Way is a historic residential neighborhood built in <a1_0><b6_0>1922<b6_0/><a1_0/> connecting <a2_0><b7_0>Downtown<b7_0/><a2_0/> with Coral Gables, and is home to many old homes and tree-lined streets. Coconut Grove was established in <a3_0><b8_0>1825<b8_0/><a3_0/> and is the location of Miami's City Hall in <a4_0><b9_0>Dinner Key<b9_0/><a4_0/>, the Coconut Grove Playhouse, CocoWalk, many nightclubs, bars, restaurants and bohemian shops, and as such, is very popular with local college students.
